[Student "E"]
{[showcards N:C3]

You are West. The bidding has been as shown.

Partner led the \H10, won by dummy's \HA. At trick 2 North calls for dummy's \C3. Which card do you play?

Play the \C6.

You would not have been expecting North to play a small \C from dummy's holding. The only way it makes sense is if North holds the \CQ.

If you play your \CK you will win the trick, but in so doing you will set up 3 \C tricks for North, which is all he needs to make the slam.

Play low instead and North will win his \CQ. But now your \C K 10 sits behind dummy's \C J 4 so he can get only one more trick in the suit, the \CA. }
[Play "W"]HT

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
